They’re BAAACK!!! A lot of things have changed in the ten years since “The L Word” ended its groundbreaking six season run, but one thing that HASN’T changed is the timeless beauty of star TheJenniferBeals. Today we’re celebrating the arrival of “The L Word: Generation Q” with Matthew’s super-glam portrait of then-emerging star Jennifer created in 1983 for Andy Warhol’s InterviewMag while she was promoting her breakout role in the ‘80s classic “Flashdance.” In contrast to Jennifer’s character Alex in that film (who works as a welder by day and exotic dancer at night), Matthew had her adorned with opulent accessories – including cocktail rings by TiffanyAndCo and a stunning marbled suede outfit by Fendi – and posed next to a vintage LouisVuitton chest. In Matthew’s world, people and things go round and round, so as a bonus, swipe left for Matthew’s 2003 portrait of the original Season 1 cast, led by (you guessed it) Jennifer Beals and her costars ErinCDu, KateOMoennig, LeishaHailey, KarinaLombard, MiaKirshner, LaurelHolloman, and Pam Grier (another MR favorite)!
